  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd support for Enumerations\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nEnum support would be broadly useful for a number of tasks, such as role mangament, [FSMs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finite-state_machine), and other types of stateful logic.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nEnumerations would be defined like follows:\r\n```python\r\nenum Roles:\r\n    itemA  # bit 0\r\n    itemB  # bit 1\r\n    ...  # bits 2 - N-1 (maximum of 256 items allowed)\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing [`IntFlagEnum`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/enum.html#intflag) as inspiration, we can enable explicit \"membership checks\" such as this Role Mangagement example:\r\n```python\r\nenum Roles:\r\n    admin\r\n    ... \r\n\r\nuser_role: HashMap[address, Roles]\r\n\r\ndef set_role(user: address)\r\n    self.user_role[user] = Roles.admin # `& Roles.other & ...` to set multiple bits\r\n    self.user_role[user] += Roles.admin  # Can use admin (use bitwise arithmatic)\r\n    self.user_role[user] -= Roles.admin  # Revoke admin (use bitwise arithmatic)\r\n\r\ndef only_admin():\r\n    # NOTE: The following actually performs `self.roles[msg.sender] & Roles.admin == Roles.admin`\r\n    assert self.roles[msg.sender] is Roles.admin\r\n    assert self.roles[msg.sender] in (Roles.admin,)  # allows multiple checks\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNo backwards compatibility issues\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nNo dependencies\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/2316#issuecomment-782721410\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
